Global Glaucoma Drugs Market Insights
Glaucoma Drugs Market size was valued at USD 6.8 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 9.6 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 4.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Glaucoma Drugs Market Overview
The global glaucoma drugs market size was valued at approximately USD 6.5 billion in 2023 and is projected to grow at a CAGR of 5.4% from 2024 to 2030. The increasing prevalence of glaucoma, growing geriatric population, and advancements in drug formulations are driving market growth. The market is categorized into various drug types, including prostaglandin analogs, beta-blockers, alpha agonists, and carbonic anhydrase inhibitors. The rise in awareness about eye health, coupled with technological innovations in glaucoma treatments, is expected to fuel market expansion. Moreover, the demand for combination therapies and personalized medicine is gaining momentum, further supporting market growth.

